title: 'encapsulation and testing : helpful'
pid: 38a571d2-991e-44c6-a4ce-eed1bf8f105b
body: |2-
  Consider the "blast radius".
  Consider how "verifiable" a process's results are.

  If only an AI understands the total structure of your program, trouble.
  But if only an AI understands the algorithm you're using
  to transform some JSON files into TOML files,
  and you have tests in place to make sure the results make sense,
  that's more likely to be safe.
